    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nnightly\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot relevant\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbob\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n`:luafile %` the file below\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.fn.getcharstr()\r\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_cursor(0, { 1, 10 })\r\n-- after this, the cursor will not be shown at {1,10}\r\nvim.fn.getcharstr()\r\n-- now it will show at the correct position\r\nprint(\"done\")\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAfter the first `getcharstr`, the visible cursor should be at `{1,10}`\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe cursor is still shown at the original position and will move to `{1,10}` after the second `getcharstr` finishes.",
